oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: World War I uniform jacket worn by Doug Dillon
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A brown, cotton U. S. Army tunic from World War I. A tag identifies the owner as Doug Dillon and states the jacket was found in a landfill. The name "Dillon" is handwritten inside the collar. There are seven U. S. Army buttons on the front and two collar discs inidcating Company F of an infantry regiment. The shoulder patch of the 78th Division is on the left sleeve. There is one chevron on the sane sleeve indicating six to eleven months of overseas service.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
